1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
What if your memories are not as reliable as you think?

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:08,400
Eyewitness accounts have shaped justice, but science reveals shocking limits.

3
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:13,200
Studies show memories can be altered, with confidence often misleading the truth.

4
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:17,600
In tests, participants recalled details differently after just a few days.

5
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:21,600
This means eyewitness testimony isn’t foolproof; it can mislead investigations.

6
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:28,800
So next time you hear an eyewitness account, remember—what we think we saw may not always be true!

7
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:31,600
Like and follow for more intriguing insights!
